.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-9::.
City: boston, san-francisco, nizza, marseilles
The people use 4 different means of transport: boat, bus, taxi, trike
1. the person traveling to boston is between the person traveling to marseilles and the person driving the boat##2
2. the person driving the trike is on the far left##1
3. the person driving the trike is on the left or right of the person traveling to boston##3
4. the person traveling to san-francisco is somewhere to the right of the person driving the boat##5
5. the person driving the bus is the person driving the bus##1
6. the person traveling to nizza is not the person driving the taxi##6
7. the person traveling to marseilles is not to the right of the person traveling to nizza##8
8. the person driving the boat is not to the left of the person driving the bus##8

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1   |     2     |   3   |    4    |
| City   | marseilles   | boston | nizza | san-francisco |
| Transport     | trike | bus       | boat  | taxi    |

